<DOC><DOCNO> AP890212-0040 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-12-89 1455EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Norway-Arsonist     02-12 0071</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Norway-Arsonist,0071</SECOND><HEAD>Fifteen Years Prison For Setting 81 Fires</HEAD><DATELINE>DRAMMEN, Norway (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A man described by officials as a lonerexcited by blue lights and sirens was sentenced to 15 years inprison Sunday for setting 81 fires from 1985 to 1988.   Tom Cato Abrahamsen, 36, was convicted of setting the fires insoutheastern Norway. No one was killed in the blazes, which causedmore than $21 million damage.</TEXT></DOC>